  "chunk_index": 12,
  "summary": "Investigators discuss the gruesome details of the murders of Ito and Uma. Nakamura reports that Ito's feet were severed approximately thirty minutes after his death. The victims' necks were cut cleanly, suggesting the use of a highly skilled blade rather than a blunt instrument like an axe. Nakamura further notes that the victims were likely knocked unconscious before being decapitated. While a guillotine was considered as a possible tool, there were no signs of its use. Kumotsuma suggests the killer is hiding the weapon to create a specific effect and to signal that more murders will follow.\n\nRegarding the crime scene at \"Hell's Gate,\" fingerprints on the door handles belong to Ito and Umezawa, suggesting Umezawa either entered the room of his own accord or was lured there. Although blood from both victims was found in \"Hell's Gate,\" a significant amount of Ume's blood was also discovered on the carpet in Ito's room. Kumagai identifies a suspicious inconsistency: Uma's left arm experienced a spasm while he was holding a key, despite him being right-handed.\n\nThe investigation establishes that Ito was killed in his room between 3:00 a.m. and 3:30 a.m., while Uma was killed at \"Hell's Gate.\" The scene at \"Hell's Gate\" presented a locked-room situation, as the door was locked and the key remained in Uma's hand. As the investigators settle into a guest room on the third floor, Mochizuki suggests that the murders are part of an ongoing series and may be related to a delegation Ito intended to pass on.",
  "summary_whitespace_tokens": 253,
